  <section id="metrics" class="private-evals-section" aria-labelledby="metrics-title">
    <div class="private-evals-section-head">
      <span class="panel-kicker">Metrics and scoring</span>
      <h2 id="metrics-title">Performance is only one part of the scorecard.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="private-evals-table-wrap">
      <table class="private-evals-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Metric</th>
            <th>What it answers</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {metricRows.map(([metric, value]) => (
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">{metric}</th>
              <td>{value}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <details class="private-evals-details">
      <summary>See calculation details</summary>
      <div>
        <p><strong>Portfolio return</strong> = sum of each holding's weight multiplied by its realized return.</p>
        <p><strong>Portfolio minus S&amp;P 500</strong> = portfolio return minus S&amp;P 500 return.</p>
        <p><strong>CapitalBench Score</strong> = portfolio return relative to the hindsight-best eligible asset return in that same window.</p>
        <p><strong>Regret</strong> = hindsight-best eligible asset return minus portfolio return.</p>
        <p><strong>Consistency</strong> = similarity of holdings and weights across repeated identical tasks.</p>
        <p>
          Performance, consistency, cost, and latency remain visible as separate fields. CapitalBench does not hide
          materially different trade-offs inside one unexplained composite grade.
        </p>
      </div>
    </details>
    <aside class="private-evals-callout">
      <h3>Success thresholds</h3>
      <p>
        CapitalBench does not automatically issue a universal "pass" or "fail." A pass/fail recommendation is included
        only when the buyer defines measurable thresholds before execution, such as minimum valid-output rate, maximum
        concentration, acceptable latency, or minimum consistency.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </section>

